properties.Name: EmblFormatSequenceValueType
properties.Description:
A potential value for a position in the EMBL file sequence.

Ex:
- SQ (The start of the sequence is marked by a line starting with "SQ" )
- // ( and the end of the sequence is marked by two slashes)
-A
-C
-T
-G

Columns.Name: EmblFormatSequenceValueTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a EMBL format sequence value type.
